summary:
The presence of bilateral tubal block at the cornua indicates poor chances of spontaneous conception, making surgical intervention ineffective. In such cases, assisted reproduction techniques like intra-vitro fertilisation (IVF) represent the most appropriate subsequent step as they circumvent the dysfunctional tube system altogether.

Final Answer:\boxed{A}

Note: Despite initial confusion over procedural validity within context, final decision rests upon alignment with recognized medical practice where IVF follows confirmed tubal obstructions—especially when both tubes are affected—and absence of support from other options in literature reviewed.

